  "body": "#### Overview of the Issue\r\n\r\nmysqlctl does not set the `basedir` when starting `mysqld`, and thus `mysqld` can not always find the `plugindir` if `mysqld` is located in an exotic location.\r\n\r\nI noticed this because I use dbdeployer, and have my `VT_MYSQL_ROOT` set to a location like `~/opt/mysql/8.0.16`.\r\n\r\nThe plugindir is required to enable semisync.\r\n\r\n#### Reproduction Steps\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce this issue, example:\r\n```\r\n+++ b/go/vt/mysqlctl/mysqld.go\r\n@@ -220,8 +220,14 @@ func (mysqld *Mysqld) startNoWait(ctx context.Context, cnf *Mycnf, mysqldArgs ..\r\n                                return err\r\n                        }\r\n                }\r\n+               mysqlBaseDir, err := vtenv.VtMysqlBaseDir()\r\n+               if err != nil {\r\n+                       return err\r\n+               }\r\n                arg := []string{\r\n-                       \"--defaults-file=\" + cnf.path}\r\n+                       \"--defaults-file=\" + cnf.path,\r\n+                       \"--basedir\" + mysqlBasedir,\r\n+               }\r\n```\r\n\r\nBy contrast, if you examine the code for when `mysqlctl` launches `mysqld` to `installDataDir()` you can see that it specifies the basedir. So it is only this location here that is missing.",
